SIMPLE: resolver
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resolver
<hw>Re*solv"er</hw> <pr>(r?-z?lv"?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>That which decomposes, or dissolves.</def>
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which clears up and removes difficulties, and
makes the mind certain or determined.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Burnet.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One who resolves, or formal a firm
purpose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resonance</ent>⟦br⟧
